    <h3 class="title"><a href="/node/405#comment-1903" class="active">Resolution</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by Kapusta (not verified) on Mon, 2006-07-24 17:55.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>Don't you think it would have to have pretty high resolution for it be really revolutionary?<br />
I mean, how many interesting varitations can you do before you get bored? I know from experience when using the Google Earth software that my curiosity makes me want to magnify more and more and more.... and I always get frustrated when it gets all pixely.<br />
The point is - the globe can only show ALL of the earth to be effectful.</p>
<p>Still - I think it's a really cool idea.</p>
</div>
